# Agent Configuration

## Skills Index

| Skill | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| memory-system | Memory API reference and usage |
| self-improvement | Self-learning and optimization |
| task-queue | Async background task execution |
| web-search | Web search integration |

## Rules

### Memory

Unified memory — PostgreSQL + pgvector + bge-m3. One entry point for all searches.

**Search: always use `memory_search` first**
- Default memory search tool, no need for user to specify
- Searches workspace files + conversation memories simultaneously, hybrid ranked
- User asks about "what did we do before" / "any record of X" / "last time" → use memory_search

**Write: use `curl`** (only for these operations)
```bash
# Store structured facts
curl -s -X POST http://localhost:18800/facts -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"domain":"...", "key":"...", "value":...}'

# Store conversation memory
curl -s -X POST http://localhost:18800/store -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"content":"...", "category":"decision"}'

# Context recall (when you need large context)
curl -s http://localhost:18800/recall -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"context":"topic"}'

# Force workspace re-index (after modifying workspace files)
curl -s -X POST http://localhost:18800/workspace/sync -d '{"force":true}'
```

**Simple rule: Search → memory_search, Write → curl**
